1. "open" the boot.
2. "fetch" the jack from the boot.
3. "fetch" the wrench from the boot.
4. "loosen" the nuts on the hub.
5. "jack-up" the hub off the ground.
6. "undo" the fastening of the nut from the hub.
7. "remove-wheel" from the hub.
8. "put-away" the flat tyre into the boot.
9. "fetch" the intact tyre from the boot.
10. "put-on-wheel" onto the hub.
11. "do-up" the fastening of the nut to the hub.
12. "jack-down" the hub back on the ground.
13. "tighten" the nut on the hub.
14. "put-away" the wrench back into the boot.
15. "put-away" the jack back into the boot.
16. "fetch" the pump from the boot.
17. "inflate" the intact tyre on the hub.
18. "put-away" the pump back into the boot.
19. "close" the boot.